He gave me two menu's. I ordered something real simple off of the lunch specials, white rice with sauteed broccoli for my girl (who is 6 like the other kids) and a fried rice with chicken and broccoli for myself. I expected to receive a bill for $13 per person like the other kids or at the very least the prices on the lunch special menu. I got a bill for $53 DOLLARS!!!  I explained to the manager that I only came with $30 and I mentioned that the agreed upon amount was $13 per person for the meals at this event and that he should have told me before making the food that it was going to be so much extra, it was wrong for them to just spring a large check on me at the end. And I also pointed out that there lunch specials weren't even that much.  The waitress starts YELLING and making a huge scene around about 120 1st graders and there teachers and parents, saying "OH he showed you this menu you new the prices (Pointing to the large menu) I was trying to explain that he gave e two menus and that I ordered my  meal off of the lunch specials and that my kids (again just white rice and broccoli) should have been $13 and she jest kept yelling  "NO, NO!!! He show you this menu!" pointing to the larger one. So the I just pulled the smaller lunch special menu I'm holding in my hands out of thin air? It's not my fault that they did not communicate the cost before hand and it's not my fault that his English was poor and apparently did not understand when I said lunch special.  This was the most appalling experience I have ever experience in a restaurant. YELLING at me loud (like over powering my voice so much she couldn't or wouldn't hear what I was trying to explain) over $23 difference for a group of over 120 people!!! TRASHY EMPLOYEES! The staff walk around with carts and tables pulled with food, and you simply stop them when you see something you like. We ordered a mass of food, based solely on sight since we couldn't find out what each dish was. There were only a few that were not delicious. The best part was the bill. For three people to stuff themselves it was less then $25.00.
